<OrgName><entry>SOUTH WEST AREA SITTING SERVICE (SWASS)</entry>
</OrgName>
<Desc><entry>A registered charity that provides free support for carers of elderly people aged 60 years and over living in the South West of the city.  Provides short-term respite care by trained volunteers for one morning/evening/weekend a week to enable carers to have a break from caring.  Carers can use the service on a regular weekly basis or for one-off occasions such as hospital appointments or outings with friends.  Sitters provide companionship and will make tea or a light meal.  Company limited by guarantee no 2730654.  Self or any referral.</entry>
</Desc>
